# FastAPI Gemini Line Bot

This project is a Line Bot built using FastAPI and integrated with the Gemini API to provide answers to frequently asked questions (FAQs).  
Check out my [Medium post](https://medium.com/@harry12345345/%E5%B0%87%E5%B8%B8%E8%A6%8B%E5%95%8F%E9%A1%8C%E9%9B%86-faq-%E8%AE%8A%E6%88%90%E5%85%8D%E8%B2%BBgemini-line-bot%E6%A9%9F%E5%99%A8%E4%BA%BA-%E7%94%A8zeabur%E5%B0%87fastapi%E9%83%A8%E5%B1%AC%E5%9C%A8aws%E4%BC%BA%E6%9C%8D%E5%99%A8%E4%B8%8A-61a1f60b9243)

## Features

- **FastAPI Framework**: The bot is built using the FastAPI framework.
- **Gemini API Integration**: Retrieves responses from the Gemini API.
- **Line Messaging API**: Communicates with users through the Line Messaging API.

## Requirements

- Python 3.7+
- FastAPI
- Uvicorn
- Line-Bot-SDK

## Installation

1. Clone the repository:
    ```sh
    git clone https://github.com/YUNHAN-LU/fastapi-gemini-linebot
    cd fastapi-gemini-linebot
    ```

2. Install dependencies:
    ```sh
    pip install -r requirements.txt
    ```

## Running the Bot

1. Set environment variables for the Gemini and Line API keys.
2. Start the FastAPI server using Uvicorn:
    ```sh
    uvicorn main:app --reload
    ```

## Usage

- Interact with the customer
